    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-02-10T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-02-10T06:00:00-05:00" n="198"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">850.33/2–1054: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 198<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d198fn1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">Dulles</persName> was in Berlin to attend
                        the meetings of the Berlin Conference.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-02-10T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 10, 1954—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dulte1">Dulte</gloss> 60. For Acting Secretary, please pass
                        <persName corresp="#p_WILSONCE2">Wilson</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="#p_HUMPHREYGM1">Humphrey</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="#p_STASSENHE1">Stassen</persName>, from Secretary. Have been
                    conferring here with <persName corresp="#p_MONNETJ1">Monnet</persName> as to how
                    to give some reality to President’s letter of June 16 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >15</hi>]<note n="2" xml:id="d198fn2">For information concerning the
                        exchange of correspondence between President <persName
                            corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">Eisenhower</persName> and Senator
                            <persName>Wiley</persName> and Representative
                            <persName>Chiperfield</persName> concerning <persName
                            corresp="#p_MONNETJ1">Monnet</persName>’s visit and the possibility of a
                        loan for the European Coal and Steel Community, see <ref target="#d172"
                            >Document 172</ref>.</note> and communiqué of December 23<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d198fn3">This is a reference to the White House press release of
                        Dec. 23 in which President <persName corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1"
                            >Eisenhower</persName> reaffirmed his hope that ways might be found to
                        enable the United States to assist the Coal and Steel Community in
                        modernizing and developing the natural resources within its jurisdiction.
                        For the text of this press release, see Department of State <hi
                            rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, Jan. 4, 1954, p. 7.</note> regarding
                    advances to coal and steel community. Believe effort should be made to reinstate
                    availability of [$]100 million payable half our present and next fiscal year,
                    but all within calendar year, but that actual form of announcement should await
                    negotiations which would give atmosphere conducive to United States support of
                    coal and steel community. <pb facs="0409" n="361" xml:id="pg_361"/> This
                    community under serious attack here by enemies of <gloss target="#t_EDC1"
                        >EDC</gloss> and European unity, and believe that some evidence of United
                    States support along lines of President’s prior communications is important at
                    this time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
